missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain points at a real mission-aligned pressure point: exact Navier-Stokes may realize some desired Tao-role channels while still failing to isolate them. But the chain treated "leakage" as if it could be chosen by bookkeeping, delayed the geometry and helicity adversary too long, and moved too quickly from forced couplings to a dynamical obstruction claim.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:29:### 4. Geometry and helicity are introduced too late, but the attacker overstates the cost of restricted hypotheses
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:33:The core objection is correct: geometry and helicity choices determine the ledger itself, so they cannot be postponed until after a lower-bound worksheet is built. Those adversarial degrees of freedom must be present when the packet class and observable are fixed. But the attacker goes too far in implying that collapse on a special family always means the theorem object is wrong. A lower bound on an explicit restricted class can still be mathematically real and mission-useful if its scope is stated honestly.
