+  `F_SS(1/12)`;
+- the canonical one-bridge packet semantics remain fixed:
+  role labels,
+  packet-level identity,
+  mandatory conjugate completion,
+  normalization,
+  sign / phase sheet,
+  desired Tao-like five-channel core,
+  and the classwise forced-extra categories
+  `mirror`,
+  `companion`,
+  `feedback`,
+  `cross`;
+- any newly used realization datum, wavevector/helicity ledger, or exact
+  coefficient identity must come with one same-currency promoted derivation or
+  explicit citation path;
+- no later theorem statement may outrun the audited realization or audited
+  family unless a genuine reduction argument is proved; and
+- if one honest audited realization cannot be frozen without changing packet
+  semantics, silently removing freedoms, or inventing a new closure
+  convention, Step 9 must stop with a source-basis /
+  no-canonical-finite-reduction memo.
+
+Return concrete findings, not just file paths, on these exact questions:
+
+1. Which local materials most sharply identify the inherited fixed ledger that
+   Step 9 must import unchanged?
